  "analysis": "All prior checkpoint calls returned 502 Bad Gateway through an external proxy (Server: oversea-squid2...), indicating curl is using a proxy instead of reaching the local service. The error shows a URL rewritten to http://program:11080/checkpoint, confirming proxy interference. We must bypass proxies when calling the in-network service. We'll use curl --noproxy '*' to ensure direct access to http://program:8008.\nNext, we need to determine the total number of lines (N) and then fix bugs. We can find N even if there are bugs because the API specifies that out-of-range requests return an error distinct from success/failure. We'll first validate connectivity with a small line, then jump to a known-out-of-range line (1,048,576) to confirm behavior, and begin bounding N with binary search.",
